### Adding and Removing Columns

Use `include=` to add presets to the base set and `exclude=` to remove them. Both accept lists of
preset names. The available profile presets are: `first_name`, `last_name`, `name`, `email`,
`address`, `city`, `state`, `postcode`, `phone_number`, `company`, and `job`.

::: {#0fdfa390 .cell execution_count=13}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Standard set + company column
pb.preview(
    pb.generate_dataset(
        pb.Schema(**pb.profile_fields(include=["company"])),
        n=100, seed=23,
    )
)
```

