### Column Prefixes

The `prefix=` parameter prepends a string to every column name. This is especially useful when a
schema needs two independent profiles (e.g., sender and recipient):

::: {#2246222d .cell execution_count=15}
``` {.python .cell-code}
schema = pb.Schema(
    **pb.profile_fields(set="minimal", prefix="sender_"),
    **pb.profile_fields(set="minimal", prefix="recipient_"),
)

pb.preview(pb.generate_dataset(schema, n=100, seed=23))
```

