### Combining with Other Field Types

Since `profile_fields()` returns a plain dictionary, it composes naturally with any other field
types:

::: {#7d271fec .cell execution_count=16}
``` {.python .cell-code}
schema = pb.Schema(
    id=pb.int_field(unique=True, min_val=1000),
    **pb.profile_fields(),
    active=pb.bool_field(p_true=0.8),
    signup_date=pb.date_field(
        min_date="2024-01-01",
        max_date="2025-12-31",
    ),
)

pb.preview(pb.generate_dataset(schema, n=100, seed=23, country="DE"))
```

